  "id": "019d343c-3cff-7f42-adb0-96b22abb129c",
  "content": "# Phase 4 Eval + Default Flip -- Decision Record (2026-03-28)\n\n## What: Evaluation framework built. Hybrid search does NOT pass ship gates. Default stays vector-only.\n\n## Key Design Decisions:\n1. Built Python eval framework (eval.py + compare.py) for A/B benchmarking via hot-swap.\n2. Fixed config_set dotted-key bug: flat \"pipeline.searchers\" keys now create nested TOML tables.\n3. Fixed tantivy hot-swap: reuse OnceLock instance instead of opening new TantivyIndex (file lock conflict).\n4. Ship gates: Recall@5 > 50% PASS (0.59), MRR > 0.60 PASS (0.73), but hybrid RRF causes regressions.\n5. Decision: Keep BM25 as opt-in. Vector + graph expansion remains default.\n\n## Review Findings Worth Remembering:\n- RRF fusion degrades source-level precision when applied to this corpus (Recall@5: 0.59 -> 0.52).\n- BM25 improves keyword recall (0.78 -> 0.86) but hurts source identification.\n- Graph expansion dominates retrieval latency (1000-5000ms), obscuring searcher-level differences.\n- Tantivy must be rebuilt after enabling BM25 for the first time (index starts empty).\n\n## What Blocked:\n- config_set dotted-key bug: pipeline config was never applied (flat TOML keys, not nested).\n- Tantivy file lock: hot-swap tried to open new tantivy while old pipeline was being dropped.\n- Both bugs prevented any meaningful A/B benchmarking until fixed.",
